SIMPLE: throne
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Throne
<hw>Throne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>trone</ets>,
F. <ets>tr⟦ocir⟧ne</ets>, L. <ets>thronus</ets>, Gr. <?/; cf. <?/ a
bench, <?/ a footstool, <?/ to set one's self, to sit, Skr.
<ets>dhara⟦nsdot⟧a</ets> supporting, <ets>dh⟦rsdot⟧</ets> to hold fast,
carry, and E. <ets>firm</ets>, a.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A chair of
state, commonly a royal seat, but sometimes the seat of a prince,
bishop, or other high dignitary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The noble king is set up in his <qex>throne</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>High on a <qex>throne</qex> of royal state.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, sovereign power and dignity; also, the one
who occupies a throne, or is invested with sovereign authority; an
exalted or dignified personage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Only in the <qex>throne</qex> will I be greater than thou.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xli. 40.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To mold a mighty state's decrees,⟦br⟧
And shape the whisper of the <qex>throne</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>A high order of angels in the
celestial hierarchy; -- a meaning given by the schoolmen.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great Sire! whom <qex>thrones</qex> celestial ceaseless sing.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throne</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Throne
<hw>Throne</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Throned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Throning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To place on a royal
seat; to enthrone.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To place in an elevated position; to give
sovereignty or dominion to; to exalt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>True image of the Father, whether <qex>throned</qex>⟦br⟧
In the bosom of bliss, and light of light.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throne</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Throne
<hw>Throne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be in, or sit
upon, a throne; to be placed as if upon a throne.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throneless</ent>⟦br⟧
